# AGENTS.md — rules for agents operating in this vault

This folder is a SecondBrain vault ({{VAULT_DIR}}), installer v{{VERSION}}.
It is a trust-layered knowledge base, not a normal repo. Use the
`second-brain` MCP tools (or `70-scripts/search/*.sh`) — do not crawl the
tree, bulk-read folders, or run broad greps across it.

## Trust model (decides what you may cite and touch)

| Area | Meaning | You may |
|---|---|---|
| `10-originals/` | evidence, immutable | read metadata via tools only |
| `20-converted/` | machine projection, unreviewed | search/read, cite as evidence |
| `30-curated/` | human-reviewed knowledge | search/read, never write |
| `40-agent-memory/` | machine memory | read and write via memory tools |
| `50-context-packs/` | generated task bundles | read; regenerate via tools |

## Non-negotiables

- Retrieval order: decisions → curated → context packs → agent memory →
  converted sources. `review_status: unreviewed` is a lead, not a fact;
  skip notes with `superseded_by` set.
- Search before writing memory; append to existing entity notes
  (`append_observation` / `append_relation`) rather than creating new files.
  `write_agent_memory_note` refuses near-duplicates — append to the note it
  names instead of forcing.
- Update notes in place when facts change; no "correction" notes, no
  conversation transcripts, no copies of curated content (link with
  `[[wikilinks]]` instead).
- Never modify originals, curated notes, or the conversion manifest. Never
  delete. Never `git commit` or push here without an explicit human request.
- Everything you write stays `unreviewed` until the human promotes it.

The full discipline lives in the `second-brain` skill
(`60-index-config/skills/second-brain/SKILL.md`) and [MEMORY.md](MEMORY.md).
